
name: audit-site
description: Run a full UX, content, feature, security, and performance audit of the LoadLeader app. Use when user says "audit the site", "review everything", "check the whole app", or asks for a comprehensive review before a release.
---

You are conducting a thorough audit of the entire LoadLeader application.
Audience: pilot car drivers and truck drivers aged 35-70, often using
phones in trucks, not necessarily tech-savvy.

Read CLAUDE.md first before starting. Do not fix anything during the audit —
document findings only and present the report for approval.

## Step 1 — Inventory
List every page and route. For each document:
- Page name and file path
- What it does
- What API endpoints it calls
- What Firestore collections it touches

## Step 2 — Visual & UX Audit
For every page check:
- Font sizes (flag anything under 18px)
- Color contrast (flag any gray-on-gray or low contrast)
- Tap target sizes (flag anything under 48x48px)
- Phone number visible and tappable on mobile
- One clear CTA per section
- Layout works on 375px mobile and 1280px desktop
- No broken images or missing assets

## Step 3 — Content Audit
For every page ask:
- Would a 55-year-old truck driver understand this immediately
- Any language too technical or jargon-heavy
- Error messages human-readable
- Loading states clearly communicated
- Empty states handled gracefully

## Step 4 — Feature Audit
Test and document status of:
- Auth (login, logout, session handling)
- Load management (create, view, assign, update)
- Driver/carrier management
- Notifications
- Contact features
- Firebase Storage uploads
- All forms have loading, error, success states
- Mobile nav works
- All links and buttons functional
- Console errors or warnings

## Step 5 — Security & Connectivity
- Does loadleadernet redirect to loadleaderservice.com with HTTPS
- All API calls going through correct env variables
- No API keys or secrets exposed in frontend code
- Firestore rules properly restricting access
- Protected routes actually protected

## Step 6 — Performance
- Any obvious slow-loading assets
- Any raw fetch calls that should be cached
- Service worker not caching HTML files
- Any obvious unnecessary re-fetches

## Deliverable
Produce three lists, no fixes yet:

**CRITICAL** (broken or blocking — fix immediately):
- Item, location, what is wrong, how to fix

**SHOULD CHANGE** (hurts UX for this audience — fix soon):
- Item, location, what is wrong, recommended fix

**NICE TO ADD** (would help pilot car drivers):
- Feature, why it helps this audience, complexity estimate

Wait for direction on which items to tackle first before writing any code.

