name: debug
description: Systematically debug a bug by reproducing it first before attempting any fix. Use when user reports something broken, says "this isn't working", "fix this bug", or describes unexpected behavior.
---

Do not guess at fixes. Follow this protocol exactly.

## Step 1 — Reproduce
Before changing any code:
- Restate the bug in your own words
- Identify the exact steps to trigger it
- Identify the expected behavior vs actual behavior
- If you cannot reproduce it from the description, ask the user
  for the missing information before continuing

## Step 2 — Locate
- Read the relevant file(s) end to end before forming a theory
- Check the Mistake Log in CLAUDE.md — has this happened before
- Check Known Issues in CLAUDE.md — is this a known landmine
- Identify the specific function or block where the bug lives

## Step 3 — Diagnose
State your theory of what is causing the bug in one sentence.
List at least one alternative theory.
Pick the more likely one and explain why.

## Step 4 — Fix
- Make the smallest possible change that fixes the bug
- Do not refactor surrounding code
- Do not improve adjacent functions
- Do not add new features while fixing

## Step 5 — Verify
- Show how to reproduce the original bug
- Show what should happen now after the fix
- If you cannot test it yourself, list the exact verification steps
  for the user
- Never claim "fixed" without proof

## Step 6 — Log
- Add a one-line entry to the Mistake Log in CLAUDE.md
- Format: `YYYY-MM-DD — what went wrong → what to do instead`
- Show the user the git commit command for both the fix and the log update

