name: read-first
description: Read and summarize a file's structure before making any edits to it. Use automatically before any edit to a file over 200 lines, or when user says "read first", "understand this file", or "before editing".
---

Before editing any file, follow this protocol.

## Step 1 — Full Read
Read the entire file from top to bottom. Do not skim.
Do not jump to the section you think needs editing.

## Step 2 — Structure Summary
Report back to the user:
- Total line count
- What the file does in one sentence
- List of major functions or sections with line numbers
- Any imports or dependencies at the top
- Any inline scripts or styles
- Any obvious patterns the file follows (naming, structure, style)

## Step 3 — Edit Location
- Identify the exact section that needs editing
- Quote 3-5 lines before and after the edit point
- Confirm with user this is the right location before changing anything
- For files over 500 lines, always confirm before editing

## Step 4 — Style Match
- Match the existing code style exactly
- Match indentation (tabs vs spaces, width)
- Match quote style (single vs double)
- Match naming conventions
- Match comment style
- Do not "improve" the style even if you would do it differently

## Step 5 — Edit
- Make only the requested change
- Do not touch adjacent code
- Do not reformat surrounding lines
- Do not add comments unless asked

## Step 6 — Diff Report
After editing, show:
- Which lines changed
- What was added, removed, or modified
- Confirm nothing else was touched
